1.java.util.Date class represents date and time in java. It provides constructors and methods to deal with date and time in java.
2.It implements Serializable, Cloneable and Comparable<Date> interface.
3.util Date also provides other date-api are java.sql.Date, java.sql.Time and java.sql.Timestamp interfaces.Thease are child interfaces of the util date.
After Calendar class, most of the constructors and methods of java.util.Date class has been deprecated.
It intraduced JDK 1, it is a legacy class.

draw backs of the date
it is not thread safe and it wont support i18N, it doesn't have timezone.